{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rs/zerolog/issues/104","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rs/zerolog","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rs/zerolog/issues/104/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rs/zerolog/issues/104/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rs/zerolog/issues/104/events","html_url":"https://github.com/rs/zerolog/issues/104","id":360586812,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWUzNjA1ODY4MTI=","number":104,"title":"BasicSampler logger should log the first message","user":{"login":"wvh","id":629882,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYyOTg4Mg==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/629882?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/wvh","html_url":"https://github.com/wvh","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wvh/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wvh/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wvh/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wvh/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wvh/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wvh/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wvh/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wvh/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wvh/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2018-09-15T23:58:55Z","updated_at":"2018-09-16T22:55:04Z","closed_at":"2018-09-16T22:55:04Z","author_association":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Right now, the BasicSampler logs every `N`'th (last) message, meaning it rotates through `N` first to log the last message of `N` because the check is after the increment:\r\n\r\n```go\r\nfunc (s *BasicSampler) Sample(lvl Level) bool {\r\n\tc := atomic.AddUint32(&s.counter, 1)\r\n\treturn c%s.N == 0\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think it would make more sense to place the increment after the check, so we're sure at least one message gets logged in case there will not be `N` messages.\r\n\r\nIn short, now zerolog does this for `BasicSampler{N: 3}`:\r\n```\r\n#1 (not logged)\r\n#2 (not logged)\r\n#3 this one is logged\r\n```\r\n... and nothing is logged if the sampler never reaches `N`.","closed_by":{"login":"rs","id":68232,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY4MjMy","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/68232?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/rs","html_url":"https://github.com/rs","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rs/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rs/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rs/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rs/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rs/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rs/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rs/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rs/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/rs/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rs/zerolog/issues/104/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/rs/zerolog/issues/104/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}